<h2>About INR to NPR</h2>

<p>
INR (Indian Rupee) is the official currency of India, while NPR (Nepalese Rupee) is the currency of Nepal.
Both currencies are widely used in cross-border trade, travel, and remittances between the two neighboring nations.
This converter provides an instant estimate based on the current market reference rate.
</p>

<p>
